Standardize URLs across both Admin (Office) and Client (Apps) portals by removing the /public/ segment from the browser address bar.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - This change affects how the web server handles requests. It is a shared hosting workaround since we cannot change the document root directly.
> - Existing links containing /public/ will be automatically redirected to clean links.

## Proposed Changes
### Configuration
#### [MODIFY] office.mybusiness.com.my/.htaccess (Root)
Replace current basic rewrite with a dual-stage rewrite:
1. **301 Redirect**: Detect literal /public/ in the request and strip it.
2. **Internal Rewrite**: Map all requests to the public/ directory.

#### [MODIFY] apps.mybusiness.com.my/.htaccess (Root)
Remove the explicit redirect to .../public and implement the clean rewrite logic similar to the Office portal.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Visit https://office.mybusiness.com.my/public/login -> Verify it redirects to [login](https://office.mybusiness.com.my/login).
- Verify static assets (images, CSS) still load correctly.
- Visit https://apps.mybusiness.com.my -> Verify it stays on the clean URL.','{\"scope\":\"Server Configuration (.htaccess)\",\"automation\":\"301 Enforcement enabled\"}','2026-02-16 06:20:12');
