Resolved a critical issue where the `/database` route was colliding with the physical `database/` folder in the project root, causing a redirection loop when `/public/database` was visited.

## Changes Implemented
- **Root .htaccess (v3)**: Added `DirectorySlash Off` to prevent Apache from forcing trailing slashes on folders that are also routes.
- **Consolidated Redirects**: Moved all `/public/` stripping logic to the root level for both portals to ensure priority.
- **Standardized Public Assets**: Restored `public/.htaccess` to the standard Laravel version to avoid conflict with root-level masking.
- **GMT+8 Sync**: Verified and ensured all system logs use local Malaysian time (Asia/Kuala_Lumpur).

## Verification Plan
- Tested `https://office.mybusiness.com.my/public/database` -> Successfully redirects to `https://office.mybusiness.com.my/database` without looping.
- Verified `APP_URL` and database-stored menu links are clean.
- Confirmed System Change Log timestamp accuracy.','{\"fix\":\"DirectorySlash Off + Root Redirection\",\"status\":\"Resolved loop in \\/database\"}','2026-02-16 07:08:05');

## Problem
- URLs like `https://office.mybusiness.com.my/public/login` were accessible
- Physical folders (`database/`, `backup/`) collided with Laravel routes causing redirect loops
- Auth middleware was redirecting to `/public/login` instead of `/login`

## Solution: Dual-Layer .htaccess Strategy

### Root `.htaccess`
- **Collision Bypass**: Physical folders that match Laravel routes (`database`, `backup`, `tests`, `storage`, `resources`, `config`, `routes`) are sent directly to `public/index.php`, bypassing Apache\'s `mod_dir` trailing slash behavior
- **Internal Rewrite**: All other clean URLs are internally mapped to `public/`

### `public/.htaccess`
- **Enforce Clean URLs**: Detects if `THE_REQUEST` contains `/public/` and 301-redirects to the clean URL
- **Standard Laravel Routing**: Handles authorization headers, trailing slashes, and front controller pass-through

## Test Results
| URL | Status |
|-----|--------|
| `/login` | ✅ 200 |
| `/public/login` | ✅ 301 → `/login` |
| `/database` | ✅ 200 (chain) |
| `/public/database` | ✅ 301 → `/database` |
| `/public/database/query` | ✅ 301 → `/database/query` |
| `/backup` | ✅ 200 (chain) |
| `/public/backup` | ✅ 301 → `/backup` |
| `/changelog` | ✅ 302 → `/login` (auth) |
| `/public/changelog` | ✅ 301 → `/changelog` |

## Files Modified
- `office.mybusiness.com.my/.htaccess` (root)
- `office.mybusiness.com.my/public/.htaccess`
- `apps.mybusiness.com.my/.htaccess` (root)
- `apps.mybusiness.com.my/public/.htaccess`','{\"strategy\":\"Dual-layer .htaccess (root + public)\",\"root_fix\":\"Collision bypass for physical folders\",\"public_fix\":\"THE_REQUEST based 301 redirect\",\"portals\":[\"office\",\"apps\"]}','2026-02-16 07:44:04');

## New Features
- **Persistent Tabs**: Open query/table tabs now persist across page reloads and browser restarts (using LocalStorage).
- **Sidebar Navigation**: Double-click any table in the sidebar to open it in a new tab.
- **Enhanced Table View**: 
  - Pagination now defaults to **50 rows** per page.
  - Seamless AJAX loading for pagination and sorting.
  - **Inline Editing** and **Row Deletion** fully supported within tabs.
- **Query Editor**: Independent query tabs with execution history.

## Improvements
- **Timezone Fix**: Changelog timestamps now correctly display in GMT+8 without double-conversion.
- **Performance**: Optimized AJAX handling for table data fetching.
- **UI/UX**: Cleaner interface with \"Single Page Application\" feel.

